                                        2634
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "The present study was performed on four individual Mn- deficient MnBi6Te1o crystals (denoted as Sample #1 - #4 henceforward; for their chemical compositions EDX) see Fig.S2).Powder x- ray diffraction (PXRD) measurements, which required grinding the crystals to a homogeneous powder, were conducted after all other measurements had been finalized, in order to elucidate the underlying intermixing phenomenon. We confirmed that all four samples exhibit the crystal lattice of MnBi6Te1o with a sequence of one SL and two QLs (Fig. 1a) plus notable cation antisite disorder. MnBi6Te1o constituted the main phase as per Rietveld method and we established a firm link between the Mn content as found by EDX and the underlying crystal lattice of MnBi6Te1o in our samples."
                                }
